02/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The government has relieved Zorica Tomic of her duties as head of Serbia's commission for co-operation with UNESCO, local media reported on Saturday (July 31st).
She will be replaced by Trivo Indjic, an advisor to President Boris Tadic.
Tomic was sacked after a scandal that revealed the state was paying a 7,000 euro-monthly rent for her apartment in Paris.
(B92, Beta, DPA - 31/07/10)
